#: ../../_docs/technical/development/environmental-variables.md
msgid "CMS_SITE_NAME"
msgstr "CMS_SITE_NAME"

#: ../../_docs/technical/development/environmental-variables.md
msgid ""
"The human-readable name of your Wagtail installation which welcomes users "
"upon login to the Wagtail admin."
msgstr ""
"O nome legível da instalação do Wagtail que dá as boas-vindas aos usuários "
"no login no administrador do Wagtail."

#: ../../_docs/technical/development/environmental-variables.md
msgid "CMS_ADMIN_URL_PATH"
msgstr "CMS_ADMIN_URL_PATH"

#: ../../_docs/technical/development/environmental-variables.md
msgid ""
"Base Path to admin pages. Do not use `admin` or an easy to guess path. "
"Should be one word and can include an hyphen. DO NOT include any slashes at "
"the start or the end."
msgstr ""
"Caminho base para páginas de administração. Não use `admin` ou um caminho "
"fácil de adivinhar. Deve ser uma palavra e pode incluir um hífen. NÃO inclua"
" barras no início ou no final."

#: ../../_docs/technical/development/environmental-variables.md
msgid "CMS_DEBUG"
msgstr "CMS_DEBUG"

#: ../../_docs/technical/development/environmental-variables.md
msgid ""
"A boolean that turns on/off debug mode. Never deploy a site into production "
"with DEBUG turned on"
msgstr ""
"Um booleano que ativa/desativa o modo de depuração. Nunca implante um site "
"em produção com o DEBUG ativado"

#: ../../_docs/technical/development/environmental-variables.md
msgid "NO"
msgstr "NÃO"

#: ../../_docs/technical/development/environmental-variables.md
msgid "False"
msgstr "Falso"

#: ../../_docs/technical/development/environmental-variables.md
msgid "CMS_PORT"
msgstr "CMS_PORT"

#: ../../_docs/technical/development/environmental-variables.md
msgid "Port to run cms"
msgstr "Porta para executar cms"

#: ../../_docs/technical/development/environmental-variables.md
msgid "80"
msgstr "80"

#: ../../_docs/technical/development/environmental-variables.md
msgid "CMS_BASE_URL"
msgstr "CMS_BASE_URL"

#: ../../_docs/technical/development/environmental-variables.md
msgid ""
"This is the base URL used by the Wagtail admin site. It is typically used "
"for generating URLs to include in notification emails."
msgstr ""
"Este é o URL base usado pelo site de administração do Wagtail. Normalmente é"
" usado para gerar URLs para incluir em e-mails de notificação."

#: ../../_docs/technical/development/environmental-variables.md
msgid "CMS_DEFAULT_LANGUAGE_CODE"
msgstr "CMS_DEFAULT_LANGUAGE_CODE"

#: ../../_docs/technical/development/environmental-variables.md
msgid ""
"The language code for the CMS. Availabe codes are `en` for English, `fr` "
"from French, `ar` for Arabic, `am` for Amharic, `es` for Spanish, `sw` for "
"Swahili. Default is `en` if not set"
msgstr ""
"O código do idioma do CMS. Os códigos disponíveis são `en` para inglês, `fr`"
" do francês, `ar` para árabe, `am` para amárico, `es` para espanhol, `sw` "
"para suaíli. O padrão é `en` se não estiver definido"

#: ../../_docs/technical/development/environmental-variables.md
msgid "en"
msgstr "pt"

#: ../../_docs/technical/development/environmental-variables.md
msgid "CSRF_TRUSTED_ORIGINS"
msgstr "CSRF_TRUSTED_ORIGINS"

#: ../../_docs/technical/development/environmental-variables.md
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"This variable can be set when CMS_PORT is not 80 e.g if CMS_PORT=8000, "
"CSRF_TRUSTED_ORIGINS would be the following: http://{YOUR_IP_ADDRESS}:8000, "
"http://{YOUR_IP_ADDRESS}, http://localhost:8000 and http://127.0.0.1:8000"
msgstr ""
"Esta variável pode ser definida quando CMS_PORT não for 80, por exemplo, se "
"CMS_PORT=8000, CSRF_TRUSTED_ORIGINS seria o seguinte: "
"http://{YOUR_IP_ADDRESS}:8000, http://{YOUR_IP_ADDRESS}, "
"http://localhost:8000 e http://127.0.0.1:8000"

#: ../../_docs/technical/development/environmental-variables.md
msgid "TIME_ZONE"
msgstr "TIME_ZONE"

#: ../../_docs/technical/development/environmental-variables.md
msgid ""
"A string representing the time zone for this installation. See the [list of "
"time zones](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_tz_database_time_zones). "
"Set this to your country timezone"
msgstr ""
"Uma sequência que representa o fuso horário desta instalação. Consulte a "
"[lista de fusos "
"horários](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_tz_database_time_zones). "
"Defina isso para o fuso horário do seu país"

#: ../../_docs/technical/development/environmental-variables.md
msgid "UTC"
msgstr "UTC"

#: ../../_docs/technical/development/environmental-variables.md
msgid ""
"[List of tz database time "
"zones](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_tz_database_time_zones)"
msgstr ""
"[Lista de fusos horários do banco de dados "
"tz](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_tz_database_time_zones)"

#: ../../_docs/technical/development/environmental-variables.md
msgid "SECRET_KEY"
msgstr "SECRET_KEY"

#: ../../_docs/technical/development/environmental-variables.md
msgid ""
"A secret key for a particular Django installation. This is used to provide "
"cryptographic signing, and should be set to a unique, unpredictable value. "
"Django will refuse to start if SECRET_KEY is not set"
msgstr ""
"Uma chave secreta para uma instalação específica do Django. Isso é usado "
"para fornecer assinatura criptográfica e deve ser definido com um valor "
"exclusivo e imprevisível. Django se recusará a iniciar se SECRET_KEY não "
"estiver definido"

#: ../../_docs/technical/development/environmental-variables.md
msgid ""
"You can use this online tool [https://djecrety.ir](https://djecrety.ir/) to "
"generate the key and paste"
msgstr ""
"Você pode usar esta ferramenta online "
"[https://djecrety.ir](https://djecrety.ir/) para gerar a chave e colar"

#: ../../_docs/technical/development/environmental-variables.md
msgid "ALLOWED_HOSTS"
msgstr "ALLOWED_HOSTS"

#: ../../_docs/technical/development/environmental-variables.md
msgid ""
"A list of strings representing the host/domain names that this Django site "
"can serve. This is a security measure to prevent HTTP Host header attacks, "
"which are possible even under many seemingly-safe web server configurations."
msgstr ""
"Uma lista de strings que representam os nomes de host/domínio que este site "
"Django pode servir. Esta é uma medida de segurança para evitar ataques de "
"cabeçalho de host HTTP, que são possíveis mesmo sob muitas configurações de "
"servidor web aparentemente seguras."

#: ../../_docs/technical/development/environmental-variables.md
msgid ""
"[Django Allowed "
"Hosts](https://docs.djangoproject.com/en/4.2/ref/settings/#std-setting-"
"ALLOWED_HOSTS)"
msgstr ""
"[Hosts permitidos pelo "
"Django](https://docs.djangoproject.com/en/4.2/ref/settings/#std-setting-"
"ALLOWED_HOSTS)"

#: ../../_docs/technical/development/environmental-variables.md
msgid "SMTP_EMAIL_HOST"
msgstr "SMTP_EMAIL_HOST"

#: ../../_docs/technical/development/environmental-variables.md
msgid "The host to use for sending email"
msgstr "O host a ser usado para enviar email"

#: ../../_docs/technical/development/environmental-variables.md
msgid "SMTP_EMAIL_PORT"
msgstr "SMTP_EMAIL_PORT"

#: ../../_docs/technical/development/environmental-variables.md
msgid "Port to use for the SMTP server defined in `SMTP_EMAIL_HOST`"
msgstr "Porta a ser usada para o servidor SMTP definido em `SMTP_EMAIL_HOST`"

#: ../../_docs/technical/development/environmental-variables.md
msgid "25"
msgstr "25"

#: ../../_docs/technical/development/environmental-variables.md
msgid "SMTP_EMAIL_USE_TLS"
msgstr "SMTP_EMAIL_USE_TLS"

#: ../../_docs/technical/development/environmental-variables.md
msgid ""
"Whether to use a TLS (secure) connection when talking to the SMTP server. "
"This is used for explicit TLS connections, generally on port 587"
msgstr ""
"Se deve ser usada uma conexão TLS (segura) ao se comunicar com o servidor "
"SMTP. Isto é usado para conexões TLS explícitas, geralmente na porta 587"

#: ../../_docs/technical/development/environmental-variables.md
msgid "True"
msgstr "Verdadeiro"

#: ../../_docs/technical/development/environmental-variables.md
msgid "SMTP_EMAIL_HOST_USER"
msgstr "SMTP_EMAIL_HOST_USER"

#: ../../_docs/technical/development/environmental-variables.md
msgid ""
"Username to use for the SMTP server defined in `SMTP_EMAIL_HOST`. If empty, "
"Django won’t attempt authentication."
msgstr ""
"Nome de usuário a ser usado para o servidor SMTP definido em "
"`SMTP_EMAIL_HOST`. Se estiver vazio, o Django não tentará a autenticação."

#: ../../_docs/technical/development/environmental-variables.md
msgid "SMTP_EMAIL_HOST_PASSWORD"
msgstr "SMTP_EMAIL_HOST_PASSWORD"

#: ../../_docs/technical/development/environmental-variables.md
msgid ""
"Password to use for the SMTP server defined in `SMTP_EMAIL_HOST`. This "
"setting is used in conjunction with `SMTP_EMAIL_HOST_USER` when "
"authenticating to the SMTP server. If either of these settings is empty, "
"Django won’t attempt authentication."
msgstr ""
"Senha a ser usada para o servidor SMTP definido em `SMTP_EMAIL_HOST`. Esta "
"configuração é usada em conjunto com `SMTP_EMAIL_HOST_USER` ao autenticar no"
" servidor SMTP. Se alguma dessas configurações estiver vazia, o Django não "
"tentará a autenticação."

#: ../../_docs/technical/development/environmental-variables.md
msgid "CMS_ADMINS"
msgstr "CMS_ADMINS"

#: ../../_docs/technical/development/environmental-variables.md
msgid ""
"A list of all the people who get code error notifications, in format `\"Name"
" <name@example.com>, Another Name <another@example.com>\"`"
msgstr ""
"Uma lista de todas as pessoas que recebem notificações de erro de código, no"
" formato `\"Nome <nome@example.com>, Outro Nome <another@example.com>\"`"

#: ../../_docs/technical/development/environmental-variables.md
msgid "DEFAULT_FROM_EMAIL"
msgstr "DEFAULT_FROM_EMAIL"

#: ../../_docs/technical/development/environmental-variables.md
msgid ""
"Default email address to use for various automated correspondence from the "
"site manager(s)"
msgstr ""
"Endereço de e-mail padrão a ser usado para diversas correspondências "
"automatizadas do(s) gerente(s) do site"

#: ../../_docs/technical/development/environmental-variables.md
msgid "RECAPTCHA_PUBLIC_KEY"
msgstr "RECAPTCHA_PUBLIC_KEY"

#: ../../_docs/technical/development/environmental-variables.md
msgid ""
"Google Recaptcha Public Key. https://www.google.com/recaptcha/about/ will "
"need a Google account for RECAPTCHA_PRIVATE_KEY and RECAPTCHA_PUBLIC_KEY "
"creation"
msgstr ""
"Chave pública do Google Recaptcha. https://www.google.com/recaptcha/about/ "
"precisará de uma conta do Google para a criação de RECAPTCHA_PRIVATE_KEY e "
"RECAPTCHA_PUBLIC_KEY"

#: ../../_docs/technical/development/environmental-variables.md
msgid "RECAPTCHA_PRIVATE_KEY"
msgstr "RECAPTCHA_PRIVATE_KEY"

#: ../../_docs/technical/development/environmental-variables.md
msgid "Google Recaptcha Private Key"
msgstr "Chave privada do Google Recaptcha"

#: ../../_docs/technical/development/environmental-variables.md
msgid "CMS_NUM_OF_WORKERS"
msgstr "CMS_NUM_OF_WORKERS"

#: ../../_docs/technical/development/environmental-variables.md
msgid ""
"Gunicorn number of workers. Recommended value should be `(2 x $num_cores) + "
"1 `. For example, if your server has `4 CPU Cores`, this value should be set"
" to `9`, which is the result of `(2 x 4) + 1 = 9`"
msgstr ""
"Número Gunicorn de trabalhadores. O valor recomendado deve ser `(2 x "
"$num_cores) + 1 `. Por exemplo, se o seu servidor tiver `4 núcleos de CPU`, "
"este valor deve ser definido como `9`, que é o resultado de `(2 x 4) + 1 = "
"9`"

#: ../../_docs/technical/development/environmental-variables.md
msgid ""
"[Gunicorn Workers "
"details](https://docs.gunicorn.org/en/latest/design.html#how-many-workers)"
msgstr ""
"[Detalhes dos trabalhadores do "
"Gunicorn](https://docs.gunicorn.org/en/latest/design.html#how-many-workers)"

#: ../../_docs/technical/development/environmental-variables.md
msgid "CMS_STATIC_VOLUME"
msgstr "CMS_STATIC_VOLUME"

#: ../../_docs/technical/development/environmental-variables.md
msgid "Mounted docker volume path for persisting CMS static files"
msgstr ""
"Caminho do volume do docker montado para arquivos estáticos persistentes do "
"CMS"

#: ../../_docs/technical/development/environmental-variables.md
msgid "./climeb/static"
msgstr "./climeb/static"

#: ../../_docs/technical/development/environmental-variables.md
msgid "CMS_MEDIA_VOLUME"
msgstr "CMS_MEDIA_VOLUME"

#: ../../_docs/technical/development/environmental-variables.md
msgid "Mounted docker volume path for persisting CMS media files"
msgstr ""
"Caminho do volume do Docker montado para arquivos de mídia CMS persistentes"

#: ../../_docs/technical/development/environmental-variables.md
msgid "./climeb/media"
msgstr "./climeb/media"

#: ../../_docs/technical/development/environmental-variables.md
msgid "CMS_UPGRADE_HOOK_URL"
msgstr "CMS_UPGRADE_HOOK_URL"

#: ../../_docs/technical/development/environmental-variables.md
msgid ""
"[Webhook](https://github.com/adnanh/webhook) url to your server that "
"triggers a cms upgrade script"
msgstr ""
"[Webhook](https://github.com/adnanh/webhook) URL para o seu servidor que "
